@endnode


@node install "Installation"

	Wiseman 1.0 installation

	
	Unpack the archive. I suppose you have done that since
	you are reading this document. Put Wiseman were you want
	it, that is the WBStartup drawer.
	
	Copy some nice cookie files to a suitable place.

	Thats it :-).

@endnode


@node usage "Usage"

	Wiseman 1.0 usage

	
	Double click on the Wiseman icon, or type wiseman in
	the shell.

	
	Wiseman will ask you to select a cookie file, this is the
	file that contains all the quotes.

	
	Wiseman will ask you to select or the name for the hash
	file. The hash file is a small file that Wiseman uses to
	find quotes really fast. If you have created one before
	with Wiseman select that file, or enter the name you want
	the hash file to have.

	
	Wiseman will now ask you if you want to save these files as
	default. This means that the next time you start Wiseman,
	the program will try to open these files.

	
	Buttons:
	Another - will display a new quote.
	File - will let you pick another file to pick quotes from.
	? - displays the about requester.
	Quit - exits Wiseman :-(.
@endnode


@node format "File format"

	Wiseman 1.0 file format

	
	Cookie file format:	
	Before each quote a pair of percentage signs are used to
	mark the start of the quote, the beginning of the next
	quote is used as end.

	Example:
	--- beginning of file ---
	A cookie file
	%%
	Murphy's Law No. 45:
	Celibacy is not hereditary.
	%%
	Graffiti:
	I'd give my right arm to be ambidextrous.
	--- end of file ---
@endnode


